%N A254604 Decimal expansion of the half of a single half-wave constant.
%C A254604 By the definition this constant takes the value 0 < x < Pi such that the horizontal line y = sin x divides the region bounded by the sine curve and the interval [0,Pi] on the x-axis into two shapes of equal area.
%F A254604 2*cos(x) - (Pi - 2*x)*sin(x) = 1, 0 < x < Pi.
%e A254604 x = 0.368305390596661399946991689932336338080760158209792727276899496553...
%t A254604 FindRoot[2 Cos[x] - (Pi - 2 x) Sin[x] - 1 == 0, {x, 0, Pi}, WorkingPrecision -> 150] (* _Bruno Berselli_, Feb 03 2015 *)
%o A254604 (PARI) solve(x=0, Pi, 2*cos(x) - (Pi - 2*x)*sin(x) - 1) \\ _Michel Marcus_, Feb 03 2015
